The paper discusses stability conditions for online learning algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions popular classes of online learners such as Follow-the-(Regularized)-Leader, Mirror Descent, gradient-based methods, and randomized algorithms like Weighted Majority and Hedge, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a new stability condition related to uniform-leave-one-out stability, which is a concept that falls under information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
